M|rules|title: Minimize Serialization at RSC Boundaries
M|rules|impact: HIGH
M|rules|impactDescription: reduces data transfer size
M|rules|tags: server, rsc, serialization, props
M|rules|The React Server/Client boundary serializes all object properties into strings and embeds them in the HTML rsp and subsequent RSC requests. This serialized data directly impacts page weight and load t
M|rules|**Incorrect (serializes all 50 fields):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|async function Page() {
M|rules|const user = await fetchUser()  // 50 fields
M|rules|return <Profile user={user} />
M|rules|}
M|rules|'use client'
M|rules|function Profile({ user }: { user: User }) {
M|rules|return <div>{user.name}</div>  // uses 1 field
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Correct (serializes only 1 field):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|async function Page() {
M|rules|const user = await fetchUser()
M|rules|return <Profile name={user.name} />
M|rules|}
M|rules|'use client'
M|rules|function Profile({ name }: { name: string }) {
M|rules|return <div>{name}</div>
M|rules|}
M|rules|```